# Entity Events

## Example: Detect Entity Damage
```java
@EventHandler
public void onEntityDamage(EntityDamageEvent event) {
    Entity entity = event.getEntity();
    if (entity.getCustomName() != null && entity.getCustomName().equals("§cBoss Zombie")) {
        event.setDamage(event.getDamage() * 0.5);
    }
}
```

## Logic
- Event triggers automatically
- Check custom name or type
- Modify damage or behavior

## Edge Cases
- Multiple plugins may listen to same event → conflicts

# Custom Drops

## Example
```java
@EventHandler
public void onEntityDeath(EntityDeathEvent event) {
    Entity entity = event.getEntity();
    if (entity.getCustomName() != null && entity.getCustomName().equals("§cBoss Zombie")) {
        event.getDrops().clear();
        event.getDrops().add(new ItemStack(Material.DIAMOND, 5));
    }
}
```

## Logic
- Clear default drops
- Add custom items
- Can include rare items or commands

## Edge Cases
- Too many drops → lag
- Make sure drop items exist
